hands_on_practices.solution:
We treat the “particles’’ (density peaks) as an effective mass $M$ at the lattice sites.  At $T=0$ only zero-point phonon motion contributes.  One finds for the mean-square displacement per site  
$$
\langle u^2\rangle
=\frac{\hbar\,A_{\rm cell}}{2M}\sum_{s=L,T}
\int_{BZ}\frac{d^2k}{(2\pi)^2}\frac1{\omega_s(k)}\,,
$$
with $A_{\rm cell}=\tfrac{\sqrt3}{2}a^2$ and $\omega_L=c_Lk,\;\omega_T=c_Tk$.  
We approximate the hexagonal BZ by a circle of area $\pi k_D^2=(2\pi)^2/A_{\rm cell}$ so  
$$
k_D=\sqrt{\frac{8\pi}{\sqrt3\,a^2}}\,. 
$$
Hence  
\begin{align*}
\langle u^2\rangle
&=\frac{\hbar\,A_{\rm cell}}{2M}
\int_{0}^{k_D}\frac{2\pi k\,dk}{(2\pi)^2}
\Bigl(\frac1{c_Lk}+\frac1{c_Tk}\Bigr)
=\frac{\hbar\,A_{\rm cell}}{4\pi M}
\Bigl(\frac1{c_L}+\frac1{c_T}\Bigr)\,k_D. 
\end{align*}
Substitute $A_{\rm cell}=\frac{\sqrt3}{2}a^2$ and $k_D=\sqrt{8\pi/(\sqrt3\,a^2)}$:
\begin{align*}
\langle u^2\rangle
&=\frac{\hbar}{4\pi M}\Bigl(\frac1{c_L}+\frac1{c_T}\Bigr)
\frac{\sqrt3}{2}a^2
\sqrt{\frac{8\pi}{\sqrt3\,a^2}}
=\frac{\hbar\,a}{M}\frac{\sqrt{2\pi}\,3^{1/4}}{4\pi}
\Bigl(\frac1{c_L}+\frac1{c_T}\Bigr).
\end{align*}
Taking the square root and dividing by $a$ gives the Lindemann parameter
$$
L=\frac{\sqrt{\langle u^2\rangle}}{a}
=\sqrt{\frac{\hbar}{M a}}
\sqrt{\frac{\sqrt{2\pi}\,3^{1/4}}{4\pi}
\Bigl(\frac1{c_L}+\frac1{c_T}\Bigr)}\,.
$$
Simplifying the numerical prefactor  
$$
\frac{\sqrt{2\pi}\,3^{1/4}}{4\pi}
=\frac{3^{1/4}}{2\sqrt2\,\sqrt\pi}
\quad\Longrightarrow\quad
\sqrt{\frac{3^{1/4}}{2\sqrt2\,\sqrt\pi}}
=\frac{3^{1/8}}{2^{3/4}\pi^{1/4}}\,,
$$
we obtain the final compact form.
